      "strengths_deep_dive": [
        "GiveDirectly's operational model is built on extreme transparency and financial resilience. The organization maintains <cite id=\"11\">11.4 months of working capital in working capital</cite>, ensuring stability even during revenue fluctuations. Their governance is supported by a <cite id=\"12\">board of 9 members</cite>, with <cite id=\"13\">75% independent board members</cite>, meeting high standards for oversight. Furthermore, their impact is not just claimed but verified through <cite id=\"14\">outcome tracking of specific metrics</cite> such as total cash delivered to households, which reached <cite id=\"15\">$146,000,000 in 2022</cite>."
      ],
      "summary": "GiveDirectly, Inc. is a pioneering humanitarian organization founded in <cite id=\"1\">2009</cite> that focuses on reducing global poverty through unconditional cash transfers. The organization operates on the principle that people living in poverty are best positioned to determine their own needs, providing them with direct financial assistance across <cite id=\"2\">multiple countries including Kenya, Malawi, and Rwanda</cite>. In the 2023 fiscal year, the organization reported <cite id=\"3\">total revenue of $140,343,295</cite>, maintaining a highly efficient model where <cite id=\"4\">91.8% of expenses are directed to program services</cite>. This direct-to-recipient approach is supported by a <cite id=\"5\">perfect 100/100 Impact & Measurement score</cite> from Charity Navigator, reflecting a deep commitment to evidence-based interventions. By leveraging mobile technology, GiveDirectly has <cite id=\"6\">delivered over $117 million directly to recipients</cite> in a single year, bypassing traditional aid intermediaries to maximize the value reaching the end user.",
